                "title": "Paid Time Off",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "Part-time employees are entitled to 12 days and full-time employees to 14 days of paid time off (PTO) a year. PTO can only be taken on the following calendar year of employment. The number of holidays accrued will depend on the quarter the employee joined."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "Casual leave: employees are also entitled to seven additional days generally used for sick leave and personal matters."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "The calendar year is calculated from January 1st to December 31st."
                    },
